body_html:
It's most likely the case that you purchased your Intel CPU before 2012. You have the following options on your existing hardware:

  1. Build TF from source.
  2. Use a slightly older TF release binary (when we supported k8-sse3+)
  3. Install an unofficial binary release created a community member: #17386 (comment)

body:
It's most likely the case that you purchased your Intel CPU before 2012. You have the following options on your existing hardware:

1. Build TF from source.
2. Use a slightly older TF release binary (when we supported k8-sse3+)
3. Install an unofficial binary release created a community member: https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/issues/17386#issuecomment-370129452
